{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e3450c86-6a0a-4b3f-8b2b-509000ba3ed2","content":"That tutorial is outdated — it's using **Xamarin.Forms** APIs, not .NET MAUI.\n\n### `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` — ❌ Wrong for MAUI\n\nThis was a Xamarin.Forms platform-specific. It **does not exist** in .NET MAUI. In MAUI, pages **automatically respect safe areas** on iOS by default — no opt-in needed. Your content will already avoid the notch/Dynamic Island.\n\n### `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` — ✅ Correct concept, but check usage\n\nThis **is** a valid .NET MAUI property on layouts. Use it when you want a view to extend *into* the safe area (e.g., a full-bleed background image):\n\n```xml\n<Grid IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\">\n    <Image Source=\"background.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n</Grid>\n```\n\n### Summary for .NET 10\n\n| Goal | Approach |\n|---|---|\n| Respect safe area (default) | Nothing — it's automatic |\n| Extend into safe area | `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on the layout |\n\nLook for **.NET MAUI**-specific tutorials rather than Xamarin.Forms ones — the API surface changed significantly.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8d954e85-e272-4dcd-8ebe-66276a03a009","outputTokens":310,"requestId":"F405:3412D:202D766:2415E86:69E81D29"},"id":"c3f739f0-b394-4b2e-a72c-28b895d1d104","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:58:25.304Z","parentId":"6f99809b-b96b-4bb2-a700-37d14b0e6ebe"}
